on the second, it's a waterfight combined with showers of coloured powder. this is not a spectator sport: as a visible foreigner, you're a magnet for attention, so you'll either have to barricade yourself inside, or put on your most disposable clothes and join the fray. alcohol and bhang (cannabis) are often involved and crowds can get rowdy as the evening wears on. celebrations are fewer in south india, though private celebrations occur among north indian communities residing in major south indian cities durga puja / navarathri/dussehara, sep-oct â€” a nine-day festival culminating in the holy day of dasara, when 